NAME
    sed - stream editor for filtering and transforming text

SYNOPSIS
    sed [options] <script> [file...]
    <input> | sed [options] <script>

DESCRIPTION
    Reads input line by line, applies editing commands, and writes
    to stdout. By default prints all lines; use -n to suppress.

OPTIONS
    -n              Suppress automatic printing of lines
    -e <script>     Add script commands (can be used multiple times)
    -i              Edit files in place
    -E, -r          Use extended regular expressions

COMMANDS
    s/pat/repl/[flags]    Substitute pattern with replacement
    d                      Delete pattern space
    p                      Print pattern space
    q                      Quit (exit sed)
    a\text                 Append text after line
    i\text                 Insert text before line
    c\text                 Replace line with text
    y/src/dst/             Transliterate characters
    =                      Print line number

ADDRESSES
    Commands can be prefixed with addresses to limit their scope:

    n                      Line number (1-based)
    $                      Last line
    /regex/                Lines matching pattern
    n,m                    Range from line n to m
    n~step                 Every step-th line starting at n

SUBSTITUTE FLAGS
    g                      Replace all occurrences (global)
    p                      Print line if substitution made
    i, I                   Case-insensitive matching
    n                      Replace only nth occurrence

REPLACEMENT
    &                      Entire matched string
    \1, \2, ...            Captured groups
    \n                     Newline
    \t                     Tab

EXAMPLES
    sed 's/foo/bar/' file
        Replace first 'foo' with 'bar' on each line

    sed 's/foo/bar/g' file
        Replace all occurrences of 'foo'

    sed -n '/error/p' log.txt
        Print only lines containing 'error'

    sed '1,10d' file
        Delete first 10 lines

    sed -i 's/old/new/g' file
        In-place replacement

    sed '/^#/d' config
        Delete comment lines

    sed 's/[0-9]\+/(&)/g' file
        Wrap all numbers in parentheses

    sed -n '5,10p' file
        Print lines 5-10 only

    sed 'y/abc/ABC/' file
        Translate a->A, b->B, c->C

    sed '/start/,/end/d' file
        Delete lines between start and end

    sed '1i\Header' file
        Insert header at first line

    sed '$a\Footer' file
        Append footer at last line

    sed -E 's/([a-z]+)/[\1]/g' file
        Extended regex with capture groups

    sed '0~2d' file
        Delete every other line

EXIT STATUS
    0       Success
    1       Error

SEE ALSO
    grep, tr, cut, sort
